<DOC><DOCNO> AP890725-0089 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-25-89 1222EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--MafiaArrest     07-25 0121</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Mafia Arrest,0123</SECOND><HEAD>Mafia Boss Tracked Down at Wedding Reception</HEAD><DATELINE>PALERMO, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   After five years on the run, a convictedMafia boss was tracked down by detectives at a wedding reception,police said Tuesday.   Vincenzo Sorce was convicted in absentia two years ago ofcriminal association and complicity in drug trafficking. He wassentenced to seven years in prison.   But his whereabouts were unknown until police spotted him at arecent wedding party in Palermo. The agents followed Sorce home,where he was living under a false name, and arrested him.   Meanwhile, police in Caltanissetta said Tuesday that 20 peoplewere arrested in a crackdown on Mafia activities. Charges includedcriminal association, drug trafficking, extortion and attemptedmurder.</TEXT></DOC>